# Install After Changes

After substantive code changes to this extension, verify with the relevant tests, then package and install the latest VSIX into both Cursor and Windsurf before reporting done.

For visual changes (table layout, row height, wrapping, selection, buttons), run the relevant Playwright spec and review screenshots before packaging. For row-height or multiline-cell changes, use:

```bash
npm run test:e2e -- e2e-端到端/row-height-visual.spec.ts
```

Review the generated screenshots under `e2e-端到端/visual-review/` before reporting the visual change as done.

Use:

```bash
npm run package
/Applications/Cursor.app/Contents/Resources/app/bin/cursor --install-extension dist-产物/csv-custom-pro-latest.vsix --force
/Applications/Windsurf.app/Contents/Resources/app/bin/windsurf --install-extension dist-产物/csv-custom-pro-latest.vsix --force
```

If either CLI is missing or the install fails, report that explicitly. Remind the user to reload both editor windows after install.
